By Segun Awofadeji in Gombe The first civilian governor of Gombe State, Alhaji Abubakar Habu Hashidu, the Matawalin Dukku, Friday passed on at the age of 74 years after a protracted illness. THISDAYchecks revealed that Hashidu died in his home around 10:30 am in Gombe, leaving behind a wife, eight children, 15 grandchildren and one great-grand child. News of the death of the elder statesman filtered in around 12 noon. Hashidu was governor of Gombe State from May 29, 1999 to May 29, 2013. He was one time Minister of Agriculture and Water Resources during the administration of former military president, Gen. Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida. He was also a one-time Commissioner for Agric in the old Bauchi State and Managing Director, Upper Benue River Basin Authority. In January 2003, Hashidu sought for re-election on the platform of the All Nigeria Peoples Party (ANPP). However, he failed to be reelected and he immediately conceded defeat and praised the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) for the conduct of a free and fair election. As at the time of filing this report, Islamic funeral prayers were being held at the Gombe Central Mosque, Emirâ€™s Palace, Gombe.